</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFA5FF8FFF67F97387AAF951" blockId="27.[168,776,1620,2091]" box="[206,244,1737,1756]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">351.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFA5FF8FFF67F95D8676F8EF" blockId="27.[168,776,1620,2091]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">
Hemicryptophytes, native with wide distribution in the Southern Cone Region of South America; previously recorded in 
<collectingRegion id="49C70DC1FFA5FF8FFE85F890857AF8CC" box="[300,548,1833,1857]" country="Argentina" name="Buenos Aires" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Buenos Aires province</collectingRegion>
but not in mountain range areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFA5FF8FFF67F8D68608F7A7" blockId="27.[168,776,1620,2091]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFA5FF8FFF67F8D686DCF809" bold="true" box="[206,386,1900,1924]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Characteristics.</emphasis>
Perennial, rhizomatous herb with tetragonal stems. Leaves glabrous, with ovate-oblong shape, acute apex and attenuate base. Flowers: terminal or subtermianl, in groups of 1–3 flowers per peduncle; corolla and anthers white. Fruit: 2 mericarps with pubescence at the top.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31990A8FFA5FF8FFCFBFD888243FCB8" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFA5FF8FFCFBFD888243FCB8" blockId="27.[813,1420,562,821]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFA5FF8FFCFBFD88848AFDC7" bold="true" box="[850,980,562,586]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Comments.</emphasis>
This is a very frequent species in the study area. It grows in full sunlight conditions with other short species in deep and moderately deep soils on grassland slopes and at the summit. This species has been described as an annual species (
<bibRefCitation id="EF92BED2FFA5FF8FFB3CFD0382DAFD5C" author="Flora Argentina" box="[1173,1412,697,721]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" refId="ref30575" refString="Flora Argentina (2017) Plantas vasculares de la Republica Argentina. http: // www. floraargentina. edu. ar. Accessed on: 2017 - 9 - 25." type="url" year="2017">
Flora 
<collectingCountry id="F31483B3FFA5FF8FFB71FD03821CFD5C" box="[1240,1346,697,721]" name="Argentina" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Argentina</collectingCountry>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
) contrary to the specimens seen in the Paititi Reserve, which are hemicryptophyte herbs as previously described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF92BED2FFA5FF8FFCE7FCA784A0FCB8" author="Cabrera AL" box="[846,1022,797,821]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" refId="ref29399" refString="Cabrera AL (1965 b) Ericaceas a Caliceraceas. Flora de la Provincia de Buenos Aires. Coleccion Cientifica Instituto Nacional de Tecnologia Agropecuaria. Tomo 4 (5). Instituto Nacional de Tecnologia Agropecuaria, Buenos Aires, 434 pp." type="book" year="1965">Cabrera (1965b)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF92BED2FFA5FF8FFB98FCA78247FCB8" author="Delprete PG &amp; Smith LB &amp; Klein RM" box="[1073,1305,797,821]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" refId="ref30228" refString="Delprete PG, Smith LB, Klein RM (2005) Rubiaceas. In: Reis A (Ed.) Flora Ilustrada Catarinense. Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues, Itajai, 349 - 842." type="book" year="2005">Delprete et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
